President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of North Carolina due to the impact of Hurricane Isaias from July 31 to August 4, 2020. Federal assistance will be provided to supplement State, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. The declaration allows for federal funding on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Myra M. Shird has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.